CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 28, 1945, pg. 13 reads: "Dear Friends - That's English for the Cheres Amies, who gave a party at the Loendi Club last Wednesday. Left to right, standing: Claire Hall, Florence Holmes, Eunice Walker, Sylvia Calloway, Frances Bell, Sarah Gibson and Dorothy Carpenter.  Seated: Dorothy Bobo, Ina Belle Jackson and Ethel Davis."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of the Cheres Amies, standing from left: Claire Hall, Florence Holmes, Eunice Walker, Sylvia Calloway, Frances Bell (Nunn), Sarah Gibson and Dorothy Carpenter; seated: Dorothy Bobo, Ina Belle Jackson and Ethel Davis, gathered in Loendi Club with glass block window in background
